This Analytics example is meant to demonstrate a few of the things you can do to analyze data stored in Google BigQuery using Python. Originally developed some time ago, I thought I&rsquo;d clean it up and post it here.
For those that aren&rsquo;t familiar with BigQuery, it is a &lsquo;serverless&rsquo; database system that is fully managed and always available. Instead of charging per environment/instance/hour of time like many cloud database systems, Google charges based on the amount of data a query processes.
